Definition.WordDefinition: backstroke \back"stroke`\ n. 1. a swimming stroke that resembles the crawl except the swimmer lies on his or her back. It is usually executed with backward-moving circular arm strokes and a flutter kick. [WordNet 1.5]
backstroke n : a swimming stroke that resembles the crawl except the swimmer lies on his or her back v : swim on one's back
